<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="436" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1489,1730]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1561,1586]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Esaki" box="[322,620,1561,1586]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436" refString="Esaki, T. &amp; Miyamoto, S. (1955) Veliidae of Japan and adjacent territory (Hemiptera-Heteroptera). I. Microvelia Westwood and Pseudovelia Hoberlandt of Japan. Sieboldia, 1, 169 - 204." type="journal article" year="1955">
Esaki &amp; Miyamoto (
<number box="[554,612,1561,1586]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436" value="1955.0">1955</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName box="[729,857,1562,1586]" class="Insecta" family="Macroveliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="436" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="tibialis" subSpecies="tibialis">
<emphasis box="[729,857,1562,1586]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">P. t. tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[894,961,1562,1585]" name="Japan" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Miyamoto" box="[1045,1322,1561,1586]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436" refString="Miyamoto, S. &amp; Lee, C. E. (1963) Water striders of Korea (Hemiptera, Heteroptera). Kontyu, 31, 33 - 47." type="journal article" year="1963">
Miyamoto &amp; Lee (
<number box="[1256,1314,1561,1586]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436" value="1963.0">1963</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation pageId="4" pageNumber="436" refString="Ye, Z., Polhemus, D. A. &amp; Bu, W. J. (2013) A taxonomic contribution to the genus Pseudovelia Hoberlandt, 1951 (Hemiptera: Veliidae) from China, with descriptions of ten new species. Zootaxa, 3636 (2), 290 - 318. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3636.2.4" type="journal article">
Ye 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[194,253,1598,1622]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436" value="2013.0">2013</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[537,605,1598,1621]" name="South Korea" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Korea</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[660,731,1597,1622]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">China</collectingCountry>
. Presented here is the first record of 
<taxonomicName box="[1139,1266,1597,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Macroveliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="436" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="tibialis" subSpecies="tibialis">
<emphasis box="[1139,1266,1597,1621]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">P. t. tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1334,1433,1597,1622]" name="Vietnam" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
. The specimens we collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[500,595,1633,1658]" name="Vietnam" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
closely match the original description of 
<bibRefCitation author="Esaki" box="[1059,1358,1633,1658]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436" refString="Esaki, T. &amp; Miyamoto, S. (1955) Veliidae of Japan and adjacent territory (Hemiptera-Heteroptera). I. Microvelia Westwood and Pseudovelia Hoberlandt of Japan. Sieboldia, 1, 169 - 204." type="journal article" year="1955">
Esaki &amp; Miyamoto (
<number box="[1288,1349,1633,1658]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436" value="1955.0">1955</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Based on the current collection data, this species has a wide distribution in the Palaearctic and Oriental regions (
<collectingCountry box="[1364,1432,1670,1694]" name="Japan" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,1706,1729]" name="South Korea" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Korea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[233,303,1705,1730]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">China</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[362,462,1705,1730]" name="Vietnam" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
